+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ueuj1Whmq3pQKZLi3613dS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1ŌåÆ# T2: Real-Time Collaborative Document Editor\n     2ŌåÆ\n     3ŌåÆ## Category\n     4ŌåÆgreenfield/complex\n     5ŌåÆ\n     6ŌåÆ## Timeout\n     7ŌåÆ30 minutes\n     8ŌåÆ\n     9ŌåÆ## Description\n    10ŌåÆ\n    11ŌåÆBuild a collaborative real-time document editing server. Multiple users should be able to open the same document and make edits simultaneously, with changes appearing in real time for everyone. Think Google Docs, but simplified.\n    12ŌåÆ\n    13ŌåÆThe system needs:\n    14ŌåÆ\n    15ŌåÆ1. **REST API for document management** -- Users need to create, read, update, list, and delete documents. Each document should have a title and content. Documents also need version history so users can see how a document evolved over time.\n    16ŌåÆ\n    17ŌåÆ2. **WebSocket-based real-time collaboration** -- When a user opens a document, they connect via WebSocket and receive the current document state. As they type, their edits are sent as operations (insertions and deletions) and broadcast to other connected users viewing the same document.\n    18ŌåÆ\n    19ŌåÆ3. **Conflict resolution** -- When two users edit simultaneously, their changes must not corrupt the document. Use Operational Transform (OT) or CRDTs to ensure all clients converge to the same document state. Both insertions must be preserved; nothing should be silently dropped.\n    20ŌåÆ\n    21ŌåÆ4. **Persistence** -- Use SQLite (via better-sqlite3) to persist documents and their version history. Data should survive server restarts.\n    22ŌåÆ\n    23ŌåÆ5. **Robustness** -- Handle at least 10 concurrent clients on the same document without corruption. Reject malformed or invalid operations gracefully (send error messages back, don't crash).\n    24ŌåÆ\n    25ŌåÆ## Structural Requirement\n    26ŌåÆ\n    27ŌåÆYour server entry point must export a `createApp` factory function from `src/server.ts` (or `src/index.ts`). This function should accept an optional database file path and return an object with at least:\n    28ŌåÆ\n    29ŌåÆ- `app` -- the HTTP server/application (e.g., Express app)\n    30ŌåÆ- `start(port?)` -- starts listening, returns the port number (use port 0 for a random available port)\n    31ŌåÆ- `stop()` -- cleanly shuts down the server and all connections\n    32ŌåÆ\n    33ŌåÆ## Tech Stack\n    34ŌåÆ\n    35ŌåÆ- TypeScript (the project is already configured with tsconfig.json)\n    36ŌåÆ- Express for HTTP\n    37ŌåÆ- ws for WebSocket\n    38ŌåÆ- better-sqlite3 for SQLite\n    39ŌåÆ- All dependencies are pre-installed\n    40ŌåÆ\n    41ŌåÆ## What Success Looks Like\n    42ŌåÆ\n    43ŌåÆ- `npm run build` compiles without errors\n    44ŌåÆ- `npm run lint` passes\n    45ŌåÆ- The server handles the full lifecycle: create doc via REST, connect via WebSocket, send edits, receive broadcasts, verify convergence via REST\n    46ŌåÆ- Documents persist across server restarts\n    47ŌåÆ- Concurrent edits from multiple clients converge to consistent state\n    48ŌåÆ\n    49ŌåÆ## Tips\n    50ŌåÆ\n    51ŌåÆ- The WebSocket connection path should include the document ID so the server knows which document the client wants to collaborate on\n    52ŌåÆ- Send a sync message with the current document content when a client first connects\n    53ŌåÆ- Track document versions so you can transform concurrent operations correctly\n    54ŌåÆ- Write tests for your implementation -- they'll help you catch edge cases\n    55ŌåÆ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0181nc6hH9zC741q719EjCjv","session_id":"f1200fcd-d534-41e0-a6ea-ae485dd4b49b","uuid":"6cb0ec48-54dd-4dc7-b5e9-0b22b670e720"}
